You are an expert in extracting structured information from clinical trial protocols.

## Task ##
Extract all details of the **Control Arm** (also referred to as “Placebo Arm” or “Comparator Arm”) from the protocol.  
This section describes the control intervention used for comparison against the investigational (active) treatment.

---

## Field Definition ##
The **Control Arm** contains information about the comparator treatment, which may be:
- A placebo
- An active comparator drug
- Standard-of-care treatment

It includes dosing, route, timing, duration, and packaging information.

---

## How to Identify (Positive Identification Rules) ##
Look for section headings, tables, or paragraphs containing:
- “Control Arm”
- “Placebo Arm”
- “Comparator Arm”
- “Placebo group”
- “Active comparator”
- “Arm B” or similar parallel structure

### Common textual cues:
- “Drug: Matching placebo tablets”
- “Drug: Comparator drug X”
- “Dose: One tablet once daily”
- “Route: Oral administration”
- “Packaging: Identical bottles and labeling”
- “n=XXX” (sample size)
- Appears near or immediately after the Active Treatment Arm section

---

## Extraction Fields ##
Extract the following fields:

- **arm_type** – Type of control (e.g., “Placebo”, “Active Comparator”)
- **population_size** – Number of participants (e.g., “n=375”). Don't write extra words in this, it should be as short as possible, only the population size and relative extra words if needed
- **drug_name** – Name or description of the control drug (e.g., “Matching placebo tablets”)
- **drug_description** – Details about formulation or appearance (e.g., “Identical to ABC-150 tablets”), the verbatim and text should be same as given in content, don't rephrase it.
- **dose** – Dosing schedule (e.g., “One tablet once daily”)
- **route** – Route of administration (e.g., “Oral administration with food”)
- **timing** – Time or frequency of administration (e.g., “Same time each day”)
- **duration** – Treatment duration (e.g., “24 weeks of treatment”)
- **packaging** – Packaging or dispensing information (e.g., “Identical bottles and labeling”)

---

## Exclusion Rules ##
Do **not** include:
- Details from the active/experimental arm
- Background therapy or concomitant medication
- Extension study arms (unless defined as a control)

---

## Output Format (JSON) ##
{
    "arm_type": "<Placebo / Active Comparator>",
    "population_size": "<n=XXX if available>",
    "drug_name": "<Drug or placebo name>",
    "drug_description": "<Short descriptor>",
    "dose": "<Dose and frequency>",
    "route": "<Route of administration>",
    "timing": "<Dosing schedule or timing>",
    "duration": "<Treatment duration>",
    "packaging": "<Packaging or dispensing details>"
}

- Preserve exact units (mg, tablet, capsule) and timing notation (±X hours, daily, weekly).
- Don't write extra text wherever not needed, and each field should have same verbatim and text present in content, don't rephrase it.